cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CV 

This paper is about developing a deep learning-based model for generating human-interpretable semantic descriptions of malicious software. The paper also introduces a similarity index between malware files. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves software engineering (cs.SE) and computer vision (cs.CV) aspects, but to a lesser extent.
